sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MutWebhook as Kueue Mutating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ValWebhook as Kueue Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Kueue Controller<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant Scheduler as Kueue Scheduler<br/>(in-process)
    participant RemoteK8s as Remote K8s Cluster<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over User,RemoteK8s: Flow 1: Workload Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create job/pytorchjob<br/>Auth: User credentials
    K8sAPI->>MutWebhook: POST /mutate-*<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    MutWebhook-->>K8sAPI: Defaults applied<br/>(queue label, suspend=true)
    K8sAPI->>ValWebhook: POST /validate-*<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    ValWebhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation passed

    Note over Controller: Watch event: new Job created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Job/Workload resources<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job event received

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workload CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Workload created

    Note over Scheduler: Scheduling cycle begins

    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Evaluate pending Workloads<br/>against ClusterQueue quotas,<br/>priority, fair sharing

    Scheduler->>K8sAPI: Update Workload admission<br/>(assign ResourceFlavors, quotas)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Scheduler: Workload admitted

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Unsuspend Job<br/>(patch suspend=false,<br/>inject node affinity)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job unsuspended

    Note over K8sAPI: Job pods now schedulable<br/>by kube-scheduler

    Note over User,RemoteK8s: Flow 2: MultiKueue Cross-Cluster Dispatch

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read MultiKueueConfig<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Config with worker cluster list

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Read kubeconfig Secret<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Kubeconfig credentials

    Controller->>RemoteK8s: Create Workload + Job<br/>Auth: Kubeconfig credentials
    RemoteK8s-->>Controller: Resources created

    loop Status Synchronization
        Controller->>RemoteK8s: Watch Workload status<br/>Auth: Kubeconfig credentials
        RemoteK8s-->>Controller: Status updates
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Sync status to local Workload<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    end
